node.text:
The way they were May 2015. Bindi was 8 months old and still the baby. It was interesting to watch Bindi at such an early age want to be the boss.

node.text:
Since Stache’s passing something incredible has happened to Dexter. He loves to sit with me, give me blinky eyes and is much more calmer now that I have given him extra attention. He comes to me for reassurance and because Teddy and Bindi tend to pair off leaving Dexter out of their bromance. 

#hobbikats #orientalshorthair #picoftheday #blackcat

node.text: That time I had @chicken_n_klink come visit back in 2018.  She supports a great cause @pawproject and if you haven’t gone to their account please do so. I’m a firm believer of never declawing a cat. In my opinion, it should be banned! My cats live happy lives indoors with their nails intact. I’m pretty good at giving them manicures and pedicures and to be honest if they rip up one of my rugs or pieces of furniture…it can be replaced. I do provide them with many scratching posts and boards and they are happy to shred them as well. It’s all good. #hobbikats #videooftheday #squad #cat #orientalshorthair

node.text:
Looking forward to visiting my extended family Ken and Laurie @kenherbig who are probably the most important people in my cat life who are the reason I’ve been able to love and live with Romeo, Caesar, Stache, Bindi, Teddy and Dexter for the past 23 years. I love you guys with all my heart. 

#hobbikats #orientalshorthair #instagram #picoftheday #love
